MonitoringLocationDescriptionText:
ACTIVATION DATE JUNE 4, 1979.  BIOTA AND SEDIMENTS ARE SAMPLED FOR HEAVY
METALS AND PESTICIDES.  HEAVY METALS INCLUDE ARSENIC, LEAD, COPPER, ZINC
NICKEL, CADMIUM, CROMIUM, AND MERCURY.  PESTICIDES INCLUDE ALPHA-       
LINDANE, ALDRIN, PP'DDE, OP'DDE, PP'DDD, OP'DDD, PP'DDT, OP'DDT, ALPHA- 
CHLORDANE, GAMMA-CHLORDANE, TRANS-NONACHLOR, DIELDRIN, ENDRIN,          
METHOXYCHLOR, PCB, PCP, AND HEPTACHLOR.                                 
     KAUNAKAKAI HARBOR IS THE PRINCIPLE PORT SERVING THE BASICALLY RURAL
COMMUNITY ON MOLOKAI ISLAND.  IT IS A COMERCIAL BARGE HARBOR WITH A 40  
BERTH SMALL BOAT MOORING FACILITY ON THE NORTHEAST SIDE OF THE WHARF.   
THE HARBOR OPENS TO THE SOUTH OF MOLOKAI WHERE A COASTAL REEF EXTENDS   
MORE THAN A MILE FROM SHORE ON BOTH SIDES OF THE CHANNEL ENTRANCE.

MonitoringLocationDescriptionText:
HULOPOE BAY IS IN THE SOUTH COAST OF LANAI, APPROXIMATELY 1/2 MILE WEST 
OF MANELE BAY, AND INDENTS THE COAST FOR ABOUT 3/4 MILE. HULOPOE BAY IS 
ONE OF THE FEW AREAS REMAINING IN RELATIVELY PRISTINES STATE. MUCH OF   
THE BAY IS COVERED WITH SAND AND IS EXCELLENT FOR SWIMMING. THE BOARD OF
LAND AND NATURAL RESOURCES, STATE OF HAWAII, HAS ESTABLISHED HULOPOE    
BAY A MARINE LIFE CONSERVATION DISTRICT.

MonitoringLocationDescriptionText:
MANELE BAY IS A SMALL INDENTATION IN THE SOUTH COAST OF LANAI 3 MILES   
SOUTHWEST OF KAIMAIKI POINT. THERE IS A SMALL BOAT HARBOR IN THE NORTH- 
EAST CORNER OF THE BAY THAT PROVIDES A HARBOR OF 4.6 ACRES PROTECTED BY 
A 570 FOOT BREAKWATER ON THE SOUTHSIDE. BERTHING FACILITIES ARE AVAIL-  
ABLE FOR ABOUT 60 SMALL CRAFTS. THE BOARD OF LAND AND NATURAL RESOURCES,
STATE OF HAWAII, HAS ESTABLISHED KEALAKEKUA BAY AS A MARINE LIFE CONSER 
VATION DISTRICT.

MonitoringLocationDescriptionText:
ACTIVATION DATE IS FEBRUARY 1, 1981.  THIS STATION IS AN EPA CORE  
STATION AND WILL BE MONITORED FOR BACTERIA AND CHEMICAL PARAMETERS.  THE
SAMPLING POINT IS LOCATED ON THE WESTERN SIDE OF A SMALL INLET BOARDER- 
ING THE MAUI SHERATON HOTEL COMPLEX.  THIS HOTEL HAS 503 GUEST ROOMS    
ABLE TO ACCOMODATE 3 PERSONS PER ROOM AND HAD AN 88% AVERAGE OCCUPANCY  
RATE IN 1980.  THE NEAREST BUILDING, OTHER THAN THE HOTEL, IS A CABANA  
LOCATED APPROXIMATELY 200 YARDS FROM THE SAMPLING POINT WHERE THERE ARE 
RESTROOM FACILITIES AND BEACH EQUIPMENT FOR HOTEL GUESTS.               
     A BEACH AND CORAL REEF EXTENDS TO THE NORTHWEST, WHILE A SHEER ROCK
CLIFF EXTENDS TO THE SOUTHEAST OF THE SAMPLING POINT ACROSS THE INLET.  
THE LAND BEHIND THE SAMPLING POINT IS A WELL GRASSED AREA USED AS PART  
OF A GOLF COURSE.  A STORM DRAIN EASEMENT FROM THE GOLF COURSE ENDS AT  
THE MAUKA SIDE OF THE INLET.

MonitoringLocationDescriptionText:
000860   KAHULUI BAY                                                    
         CLASS A  COASTAL REENTRANT                                     
         OCEAN                                                          
         SOME FRESH WATER SEEPAGE BUT NO SIGNIFICANT STREAM OR          
         SPRING DISCHARGE KNOWN.  BREAKWATERS ON EACH SIDE OF BAY       
         PROTECTS KAHULUI HARBOR.  SANITARY SEWAGE OUTFALLS OUTSIDE     
         OF THE HARBOR, AT BASE OF EAST BREAKWATER AND QUARTER MILE     
         OF THE WEST BREAKWATER.  THERMAL POWER PLANT DISCHARGE         
         (MAUI ELECTRIC CO.) AT SEA SURFACE OUTSIDE THE HARBOR.         
         SOME PROCESSED WASTEWATER FROM PINEAPPLE CANNERY (MAUI PINE-   
         APPLE CO.) DISCHARGED THRU SEWER OUTFALLS.
